data: {"type":"response.content_part.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_008ae899014439f4006998a7e368708195bd852e8438283e6c","output_index":2,"part":{"type":"output_text","annotations":[],"logprobs":[],"text":"Contoso Electronics’ **Whistleblower Policy** is intended to maintain a safe and transparent workplace and **encourages employees (and contractors/third parties) to report illegal, unethical, or policy-violating activity**. Key points:  \n\n- **Who it applies to:** All employees, contractors, and other third parties.  \n- **What a whistleblower is:** Anyone reporting activity that is illegal, unethical, or not in accordance with company policy.  \n- **How to report:**\n  1. Contact **Human Resources**\n  2. Email the **Compliance Officer** at **compliance@contoso.com**\n  3. Call the **Compliance Hotline** at **1-800-555-1212**\n  - **Anonymous reporting:** Allowed via the hotline (**1-800-555-1212**).\n- **What to include in a report:** Time/date, who was involved, what happened, and any supporting evidence.\n- **No retaliation:** Retaliation is strictly prohibited; retaliators are subject to discipline up to termination.\n- **Confidentiality:** Whistleblower identity kept confidential to the extent permitted by law.\n- **Investigations:** Reports will be investigated promptly and thoroughly.  "},"sequence_number":260}

